ce:section.ce:para:
Fig. 9
 (a) shows the binding model of β-CD-NGQDs and L-Trp. It can be seen from the figure that the O atom in the β-CD structure can form three hydrogen bonds with the N atom in the L-Trp molecular structure (see Table 1
). Fig. 9 (b) is the binding model of β-CD-NGQDs and D-Trp. It can be seen that the O atom in the β-CD structure can form two hydrogen bonds with the N atom in the D-Trp molecular structure (see Table 2
). Fig. 9 (c) shows the comparison of the binding model of β-CD-NGQDs with L-Trp and D-Trp. Concerning the calculated binding energy value, the binding effect of β-CD-NGQDs and L-Trp can be judged. The force is greater than its binding force with D-Trp, which is consistent with the electrochemical recognition results.
